What Your Bot Actually Does
Protocol Zero is an AI-powered crypto trading agent. Here's the plain truth:

What it does right now:
1. Watches the market — pulls real-time price data (candles, volume,     RSI) from Binance for pairs like BTC/USDT, ETH/USDT, SOL, etc.
2. Thinks about it — sends that data to Amazon Nova (AI) which analyzes patterns and says "BUY", "SELL", or "HOLD" with a confidence score
3. Checks itself — runs 8 risk checks before every trade (position too big? daily loss limit hit? confidence too low?
4. Signs the trade — creates a cryptographically signed EIP-712 intent (like a tamper-proof receipt)
5. Registers on-chain — mints an identity NFT on Ethereum (Sepolia testnet) so the bot has a verifiable on-chain reputation
6. Tracks everything — performance metrics, audit trail, every decision sealed with a hash.


How to make real money with it:
Right now you can't — and here's why:

It's on Sepolia testnet (fake ETH, no real money)
The AI makes decent directional calls but it's not backtested over months
There's no actual DEX integration (it signs intents, it doesn't swap tokens on Uniswap yet)
To get there, you'd need to:

Connect to a real DEX — add Uniswap/1inch swap execution so the signed intents actually buy/sell tokens
Switch to mainnet — change the RPC from Sepolia to Ethereum mainnet (or Base/Arbitrum for cheaper fees)
Fund the wallet — put real ETH + USDT in the agent's wallet





